cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

This paper is about using deep learning techniques for pixel-level labelling tasks, specifically semantic segmentation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a new form of convolutional neural network that combines the strengths of CNNs and CRFs, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the use of CRFs as a probabilistic graphical model could place it in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with natural language processing tasks, which could make it relevant to cs.CL (Computation and Language).
